Ghanaian veteran rapper, Sarkodie is set to unleash a new single titled ‘Come back’ featuring afro-fusion singer, Moelogo. <img src="https://notjustok.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/5607FB1F-7F37-4FA4-87FC-B4E223C93AAE-420x420.jpeg"/> Sarkodie took to his Instagram page on the 7th of January 2021 to make the announcement. The single was initially scheduled to drop on the 8th of January 2021. He said; “A beautiful short story “Come Back” ft @moelogoProd by @mogbeatz … I know y’all will enjoy this … changed release date from tomorrow to tonight <img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/12.0.0-1/72x72/1f60a.png" alt="😊"/> <img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/12.0.0-1/72x72/1f3a5.png" alt="🎥"/>: @geneadu” <img src="https://notjustok.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/B2BB0031-2B43-474F-B1DB-50B238B9C5CD-scaled.jpeg"/> The artiste didn’t state the reason behind dropping the single earlier than expected. The song was produced by MOG Beatz. <img src="https://notjustok.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/2ACB0FF6-428C-48EE-8782-8475126C20E3-425x420.jpeg"/> The post Sarkodie Set To Drop New Single, 'Come Back' with Moelogo appeared first on Most Trusted Voice in Music & Afrobeats from Nigeria & Africa | Notjustok. Original Article Get all the Latest news, Breaking headlines,Sport, Education, Finance, Gists, Jobs, Music/Video, Technology and Top stories in real time in Nigeria and around the world.